## The Listening Device

The most important method in UI development is **`.addEventListener()`**.

You attach this method to an element, tell it exactly what 'Event' to listen for, and provide the function you want to run when that event happens.

```javascript
let myBtn = document.querySelector("#submit-btn");

// We are waiting for a 'click' event!
myBtn.addEventListener("click", function() {
  console.log("The button was finally clicked!");
});
```

The code block stays completely dormant until a click occurs!

slides.codeSnippet:
let counterDisplay = document.querySelector("#counter");
let clickBtn = document.querySelector("#click-here");
let count = 0;

// Every time a click happens, update the data AND update the DOM!
clickBtn.addEventListener("click", function() {
  count++;
  counterDisplay.textContent = "Score: " + count;
});

