## Hidden Data

When a user triggers an event (like clicking), the browser magically generates a massive data object containing details about the action (e.g., exact screen coordinates of the mouse click, which key was pressed).

JavaScript automatically passes this 'Event Object' into your function's parameter. Usually, developers just name it `e`.

```javascript
document.addEventListener("keydown", function(e) {
  // What specific keyboard key did they press?
  console.log("User pressed: " + e.key);
});
```
